An Act relative to Stony Brook Reservation.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Notwithstanding any general or special law to the contrary the department of
2 conservation and recreation shall study and make recommendations to restore and maintain
3 Stony Brook Reservation located in the city of Boston and town of Dedham. Stony Brook
4 Reservation is a historic landmark offering outdoor recreational facilities. Said report shall
5 consider the improvements to recreational facilities and the maintenance, and rehabilitation of
6 current state-owned land. Said report shall also identify long term expansion and rehabilitation
7 of the current Stony Brook Reservation to maximize public use. Said report shall be filed with
8 the joint committee on the environment, natural resources and agriculture and the house and
9 senate committee on ways and means 90 days after the passage of this act.
